# Clinical Report Processing Portal (Frontend Only)

**Stack**: HTML, CSS, Vanilla JS

This is a clean, responsive UI for a hackathon prototype where **physicians upload reports** and a **Python backend** performs:
- OCR (e.g., Tesseract) to extract **text / numbers / images**
- Numerical algorithm/ML to produce an **algorithmic conclusion**
- Image classification model to produce an **AI classification conclusion**
- Returns both conclusions and artifacts to show on the results screen.

> ✅ Your teammate will provide the Python backend. This repo is **frontend only** with clear API contracts your backend can follow.

---

## Quick start (no backend)
Open `index.html` directly in your browser and click **“Try Demo (no backend)”** to see the UI flow using `mock/sample_response.json`.

> If loading `mock/sample_response.json` is blocked by CORS when running from file://, use a tiny static server (e.g. `python -m http.server 5500`) and visit `http://localhost:5500/`.

## Wire up your Python backend
By default, the app sends requests to the **same origin**. If your backend runs on another port (e.g., `http://localhost:8000`), edit the first line in `app.js`:

```js
const API_BASE = "http://localhost:8000"; // your FastAPI/Flask base
```

### Expected endpoints (contract)
```
POST /api/reports
  multipart/form-data: patient_name, patient_id, file
  -> { "job_id": "abc123" }

GET /api/reports/:job_id
  -> {"status":"processing","progress":0-100}
  -> when done:
     {
       "status": "done",
       "extracted": {
         "text": "...",
         "numbers": { "bp_sys": 120, "bp_dia": 75, "hr": 68 },
         "images": ["/api/files/img1.png", "/api/files/img2.png"]
       },
       "conclusions": {
         "algorithm": "…",
         "ai_classification": "…"
       },
       "report_url": "/api/files/report.pdf"
     }

GET /api/files/:name
  -> serves extracted images/report
```

### Suggested Python stack
- **FastAPI** for endpoints and automatic OpenAPI docs
- **Tesseract OCR** via `pytesseract` for text
- **pandas / numpy / scikit-learn** or your custom model for number-based summary
- **PyTorch / TensorFlow** for image classification
- Store temporary files in a `jobs/{job_id}/…` folder; stream images via `StaticFiles`

## UI features
- Drag-and-drop uploader with progress
- Status polling
- Two conclusion panels: *Algorithmic* and *AI Classification*
- Pretty rendering of extracted text, numbers (key/value), and a gallery of extracted images
- "Open Processed Report" button
- Fully responsive, clean design using pure CSS

## Assets
School and hospital logos are placed under `assets/` and shown in the header.

